# GitHub sync (Personal Website)

Remote: `https://github.com/Miyeon-0131/Personal-Website.git`, branch `main`.

After completing any task that modifies project files:

1. Run `git status` and `git diff` to review changes.
2. Stage and commit with a clear, concise message (English is fine).
3. Push to `origin main` (`git push origin main`).
4. Briefly tell the user the push succeeded and include the repo URL if relevant.

Do not skip push when there are committed changes to publish.

Git identity: if commit fails due to missing author, set author via environment variables for that command only (do not run `git config --global`).

Never force-push to `main`. Do not commit secrets (`.env`, credentials).
